                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "(a.min(), a.max())"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ".  Values outside the range are\nignored. The first element of the range must be less than or\nequal to the second. "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "range"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " affects the automatic bin\ncomputation as well. While bin width is computed to be optimal\nbased on the actual data within "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "range"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", the bin count will fill\nthe entire range including portions containing no data."
