  "notes": "Binning; cost = n*ceil(log2(bins)).",
  "notes_sections": [
    "All but the last (righthand-most) bin is half-open.  In other words, if `bins` is::",
    "[1, 2, 3, 4]",
    "then the first bin is ``[1, 2)`` (including 1, but excluding 2) and the second ``[2, 3)``.  The last bin, however, is ``[3, 4]``, which *includes* 4."
  ],
  "numpy_ref": "np.histogram",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "body": [
        "Input data. The histogram is computed over the flattened array."
      ],
      "name": "a",
      "type": "array_like"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "If `bins` is an int, it defines the number of equal-width",
        "bins in the given range (10, by default). If `bins` is a",
        "sequence, it defines a monotonically increasing array of bin edges,",
        "including the rightmost edge, allowing for non-uniform bin widths.",
        "",
        "If `bins` is a string, it defines the method used to calculate the",
        "optimal bin width, as defined by `histogram_bin_edges`."
      ],
      "name": "bins",
      "type": "int or sequence of scalars or str, optional"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "The lower and upper range of the bins.  If not provided, range",
        "is simply ``(a.min(), a.max())``.  Values outside the range are",
        "ignored. The first element of the range must be less than or",
        "equal to the second. `range` affects the automatic bin",
        "computation as well. While bin width is computed to be optimal",
        "based on the actual data within `range`, the bin count will fill",
        "the entire range including portions containing no data."
      ],
      "name": "range",
      "type": "(float, float), optional"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "An array of weights, of the same shape as `a`.  Each value in",
        "`a` only contributes its associated weight towards the bin count",
        "(instead of 1). If `density` is True, the weights are",
        "normalized, so that the integral of the density over the range",
        "remains 1.",
        "Please note that the ``dtype`` of `weights` will also become the",
        "``dtype`` of the returned accumulator (`hist`), so it must be",
        "large enough to hold accumulated values as well."
      ],
      "name": "weights",
      "type": "array_like, optional"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "If ``False``, the result will contain the number of samples in",
        "each bin. If ``True``, the result is the value of the",
        "probability *density* function at the bin, normalized such that",
        "the *integral* over the range is 1. Note that the sum of the",
        "histogram values will not be equal to 1 unless bins of unity",
        "width are chosen; it is not a probability *mass* function."
      ],
      "name": "density",
      "type": "bool, optional"
    }
